The paper deals with decoding algorithms for algebraic geometric (AG) codes, which are a type of error-correcting codes used in information theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the computational complexity of the proposed algorithm, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of Grobner bases in the algorithm could also place it in cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
